The paper focuses on investigating how Lean internal startups facilitate software product innovation in large companies, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The study also examines the enablers and inhibitors of Lean internal startups, which could be relevant to the cybernetics (cs.CY) and computer engineering (cs.CE) sub-categories. The use of the method-in-action framework and the Lean-Internal Corporate Venture model could be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
